description:
**CO\-Energy** is growing and we need a full\-time **Human Resources Generalist** to support that growth.



For almost 39 years, CO\-Energy (A Connell Oil, Inc. company) has been a leading provider of fuels and lubricants to commercial, agricultural and government customers across the Pacific Northwest. As our customer base grows, we need to expand the HR team to provide excellent support to our internal customers \- our valued employees.



Please check out our website for information about our company: www.connelloil.com



Based at our Pasco corporate office, the HR Generalist will support the HR Manager as well as provide some limited support to the Chief Operating Officer (COO). Standard work schedule is Monday \- Friday, 7:30 am to 4:30 pm. Some overtime might occasionally be required in order to meet deadlines and customer needs.

 **Essential Tasks, Duties and Functions:**


* Service as the front\-line HR contact for CO\-Energy employees;
* Assist employees with routine payroll, timekeeping and benefits related questions;
* Handle sensitive employee information with a high level of confidentiality and discretion;
* Support recruiting, hiring and onboarding processes;
* Organize and maintain electronic and physical employee files;
* Track cyclical government compliance regulations;
* Other tasks as assigned to support the corporate administration group




**Minimum Qualifications:**


* At least two (2\) years of general human resources work experience, or an Associates degree in a relevant course of study in lieu of work experience;
* At least two (2\) years of customer (internal and/or external) service experience;
* Proficiency with standard office software (e.g, MS office Suite or equivalent)




**Preferred Qualifications:**


* Three (3\) or more years of general human resources work experience, or a Bachelors degree in a relevant course of study in lieu of work experience;
* SHRM or HRCI professional certification;
* Direct experience with HRIS and payroll systems




**Required Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:**


* Ability to present a supportive and professional image to both internal and external customers;
* Strong time management and problem solving skills;
* Strong interpersonal skills that demonstrate the ability to interact effectively with employees at all levels of the organization




**Work Environment \& Physical Requirements:**


* Typical office environment with prolonged periods or sitting, computer use and telephone interaction;
* Occasional lifting of office materials (up to 20 pounds)




**Compensation:**


* Hourly pay range of $28 to $32;
* Annual performance bonus and hourly rate increases
* Paid holidays \- seven (7\) per year;
* Paid Time Off (PTO) \- 128 hours per year, accrued at the rate of about 10 hours per month;
* Employee discounts on products we sell including fuel for your personal vehicles;
* Medical, Dental, Vision and Life Insurance;
* 401(k) retirement plan with employer match after one year of employment




*CO\-Energy will consider all applicants for open positions without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, military status or any other applicable protected status.*



To apply for this position, click the blue "Apply for this Job" button in the upper\-right corner.

**Who We Are:**





SEIU 775 Benefits Group’s mission is to improve the skills, health and stability of the caregiver workforce through innovation and high\-quality benefits and programs. We intend to make caregiving a health care job of choice.



 We partner with workers, employers and industry stakeholders to collectively solve workforce problems through innovation, creativity and an evidence\-based approach. Together, we deliver high\-quality benefits and services to support a growing caregiver workforce.


We are a nonprofit – passionate about revolutionizing the future of in\-home care, and are looking for others to join our smart, collaborative and kind team.



**The Details:**


**In\-Office Requirements:** This role requires up to 15% presence at our Downtown Seattle headquarters, Standard business hours Monday–Friday, 8:30 a.m.–5:00 p.m.


**Remote Work Eligibility:** For employees residing outside of the Seattle metropolitan area, remote work may be considered in the following states: AZ, CA, CO, ID, OR, or WA. Final approval is determined through a management review process.


**Category:** Full\-Time, FLSA Exempt, Regular, Non\-Union



Physical Requirements: Must be able to perform tasks that may require prolonged periods of sitting or standing, with or without reasonable accommodation.





**About the Position:**  



Reporting to the Managing Director of Equity and Learning, the Director of Employee Experience \& Development is a strategic leader and hands\-on practitioner responsible for bringing our organization to life through engaging employee experiences, robust performance management systems, and comprehensive talent development strategies. This role leads initiatives that enhance engagement, strengthen organizational culture, support professional growth, and build the infrastructure needed to develop and retain an engaged workforce.



 You will take ownership of the organization's employee engagement strategy, including our multi\-year Gallup partnership, and translate insights into creative programming that fosters connection, recognition, and belonging in a mostly remote culture. As the subject matter expert in performance management and learning strategy, you will work with Learning and Development, People Operations and organizational people partners to strengthen and optimize systems that drive accountability, growth, and alignment with organizational goals. You will also provide strategic guidance and mentorship while partnering closely with Marketing and Communication and Workplace Committee groups to ensure all people initiatives reflect our mission, values, and commitment to inclusivity and equity.



This role requires a systems thinker who can take initiative, balance strategic vision with tactical execution, understands how to build people systems from the ground up while keeping the human experience at the center of everything we do. This role will also manage the Manager of Learning and Development and the Manager of Equity and Language Access.




**You Will:**


* Lead employee engagement strategy, including Gallup partnership management, surveys, action planning, and continuous improvement;
* Design and collaborate on programs, events, and recognition initiatives that strengthen culture, foster connection, and celebrate achievements;
* Strengthen and optimize existing performance management infrastructure (currently managed through UKG), including enhancing review processes, implementing robust goal\-setting frameworks and co\-developing clear career pathways with HR;
* Lead learning and development strategy and provide direction for our leadership and staff development programs that are equity\-centered and culturally responsive;
* Develop succession planning strategy for key leadership roles, ensuring diverse talent is identified, developed, and supported for advancement across the organization;
* Provide Strategic leadership and direction towards our localization vision, ensuring alignment with organizational goals;
* Establish metrics to measure learning engagement, performance, and effectiveness;
* Use data from surveys, performance metrics, and evaluations to identify trends, inform strategies, and demonstrate ROI;
* Manage departmental budget and resource allocation to maximize impact and sustainability of engagement, performance, and learning initiatives;
* From time to time, perform other duties commensurate with the level of this position.




**You Will Need to Have:**




**Required Leadership Competencies**





**Managing with Vision and Purpose:**




Connect their work and the work of teams they lead to the organization’s Mission, Vision, and Values.




**Advancing Diversity:**




Supports equitable and fair treatment and opportunity for all.




**Courage:**




Is not afraid to take action when necessary, accepts critical feedback that is shared with the team without being defensive and incorporates feedback into their work.




**Strategic Agility:**




Sees ahead clearly; can anticipate future consequence and trends accurately.




**Decision Quality:**




Makes good decisions in the appropriate amount of time based upon a mixture of analysis, wisdom, experience, and judgement.




**Building Effective Teams:**




Blends people into teams when needed; creates strong morale and spirit in their teams, while creating a collaborative environment.




* Bachelor's degree in HR, Organizational Development, Learning and Development or related field;
* 7\+ years in employee engagement and talent development, with 5\+ years focused on designing and executing robust engagement and talent programs;
* Proven expertise and deep understanding of performance management, employee engagement, and overall culture and how these elements shape how people feel, work, and excel in the workplace;
* Strong project management, communication, coaching, and analytical skills;
* Experience navigating remote and distributed environments, building connections, and belonging across time zones and teams;
* Effective collaboration skills and the ability to genuinely build credibility and trust across all levels of the organization.




**It Will Be Great if You Have:**


* Familiarity with union environments and labor\-management partnerships;
* Proficiency in engagement platforms and learning management systems (Gallup and/or UKG experience are a plus);
* Experience working with or deep understanding of caregivers, healthcare workers, direct care workforce, or frontline service populations.




**Salary Range:**


* $124,275 to $166,796


**Benefits:**


* Fully Paid Medical, Dental and Vision;
* 18 days PTO, 15 Sick days, 9 holidays, 1 floating holiday, 2 personal days
* End of the year winter break; mid\-year summer break and earned paid longevity sabbatical
* Defined Benefit Pension Plan and 401(k) options;
* Fitness, cell phone, internet and furniture stipends.




**Statement of Affirmative Action**


*SEIU 775 Benefits Group is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an Affirmative Action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, or Veteran status.*

Cascade AIDS Project (CAP) is a trailblazer in compassionate, community\-centered healthcare. As the oldest and largest AIDS Service Organization in Oregon and Southwest Washington, CAP has been at the forefront of advocacy, innovation, and inclusive care for decades. Driven by a bold mission to promote well\-being and advance equity, CAP delivers affirming health and wellness services for LGBTQ\+ people, individuals affected by HIV, and anyone seeking respectful, compassionate care. Every program is rooted in dignity, access, and the belief that everyone deserves to thrive. Through its family of programs Prism Health, Our House, Tod’s Corner, and Esther’s Pantry CAP provides comprehensive support ranging from primary healthcare and HIV services to housing, nutrition, and community\-based resources. Together, these programs create a powerful network of care that uplifts lives and strengthens communities.


Prism Health, Our House, Tod’s Corner and Esthers Pantry are all apart of CAP. To learn more about us please visit CAP, Prism Health and Our House.


**Cascade AIDS Project** **is excited to announce that we are hiring skilled and team\-oriented Senior Director of People and Culture.** The Senior Director of People and Culture (SDPC) will lead the organization’s people and culture team and support equity initiatives to create a sustainable and healthy organizational culture that aligns with CAP’s core values and strategic direction. This includes CAP’s commitment to being a high\-functioning, supportive, diverse, anti\-racist, equitable, and inclusive organization.


The people and culture team, including two (2\) P\&C Business Partners, the HR and Payroll Administrator, the Volunteer Manager, and the P\&C Generalist, will report to the Senior Director of People and Culture for day\-to\-day supervision. The SDPC will report to the Chief Executive Officer and be part of the Executive Leadership Team.


This is a Full\-Time role working at our Davis St. location in the Old Town area of Portland. Some travel to our other offices may be required. The schedule for this role is a **Hybrid Monday\-Friday 8:30am\-5:00pm 3 days in office and 2 days work from home**.


**Starting pay for this position is $115,000 a year.**

Who You Are


* Certified as either SHRM\-SCP or SPHR or ability and commitment to obtain this.
* Bachelor's degree in a related field or commensurate experience (2 years of additional managerial HR work experience);
* At least 8 years of senior / executive level human resource experience preferably at a nonprofit, healthcare organization with at least 100 employees;
* A deep understanding of Human Resource compliance in both Oregon and Washington;
* Experience that demonstrates fluency engaging with communities of color, LGBTQ\+ communities, and communities impacted by HIV OR a willingness to learn about these communities;
* Direct experience supervising a team;
* Direct experience with labor relations preferably at a nonprofit organization;
* Exceptional leadership, project management, and organizational skills;

What You’ll Do


* Function as a strategic advisor to the ELT on key organizational and management issues.
* In partnership with the P\&C Business Partners, lead and manage all aspects of labor relations;
* Lead union bargaining initiatives and provide strategic guidance and support to Managers and P\&C Business Partners on union\-related matters;
* In partnership with the ELT and P\&C Business Partners, help define the overarching vision, identity, and strategy to continually strengthen CAP’s culture and practices and meet organizational goals;
* Create and implement organizational development initiatives that enhance CAP’s workplace culture;
* Participate and engage in trainings, workshops, and team discussions.
* Utilize Asana project management software to organize and lead projects for the P\&C team;
* Manage annual and multi\-year projects for the P\&C team;
* On occasion, prepare monthly and quarterly reports on organizational progress for the ELT (e.g. CEO, CFO), Board, and others as needed.





At Cascade AIDS Project, we believe in unlocking potential. If you believe you may have the skills to do a job, we encourage you to apply even if you don’t meet every qualification. Cascade AIDS Project is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. We comply with all relevant anti\-discrimination laws.
Employee Benefits


* Vacation \& Health Leave
* Retirement
* Medical, Dental, \& Vision
* Life Insurance, Disability, \& Family Leave

For more details about our benefits please visit our careers page capnw.org/careers


CAP cares about the safety of our team members and clients. All new employees are required to provide proof of vaccination status to HR at the time of hire (unless a documented medical or religious exemption is requested and approved).
